<div id="PJA11d136" class="doc letter">

<h2>From Philippe Andr Joseph de Ltombe</h2>

<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Paris, 28. fevrier 1781</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Il y a dix jours que lhonorable M. Searle ma remis la Lettre que votre Excellence ma fait lhonneur de mcrire le trois janvier dernier.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA11d137n1" id="PJA11d137n1-ptr">1</a> Je nai pu y rpondre sur le champ parce que des occupations, des Courses, mille Embarras ne me lont pas permis. Mais jai vu M. Searle aussi souvent que je lai pu, et je veut bien des graces  votre Excellence et de son souvenir et de mavoir procur la Connoissance dun Citoyen aussi estimable que M. Searle. Mon regret de ne pouvoir Le cultiver plus Longtems est infini; mais il part incessamment pour La hollande et je pars pour lAmrique dans douze jours.</p>
<p>Je propose  votre Excellence de mhonorer de ses ordres pour Philadelphie et Boston. Je Crois quElle est bien sre que je macquiterai de tout ce dont Elle me chargera avec beaucoup de Zle et dempre-<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-11-02-pb-0167">[167<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-11/ADMS-06-11-02-pb-0167.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>ssement. Je lui demande encore ses recommendations comme choses qui mhonoreront infiniment auprs de ses Compatriotes et je prie votre Excellence de vouloir bien madresser son Paquet, le pltt possible,  Paris o je Le trouverai  mon retour dun voyage de dix jours que je dois faire.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA11d137n2" id="PJA11d137n2-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>Je vous prie, Monsieur, de vouloir bien agrer Les hommages du Respect et dun tendre attachement avec Les quels je suis de Votre Excellence, Le trs humble et trs obeissant Serviteur</p>
<div class="closer">
<div class="signed-multiple">
    <p class="signed multiple">De Ltombe<br/>Ecuyer, Consul gnral de France  Boston.<br/>Rue de lUniversit  Paris.</p>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="PJA11d137" class="trans letter">

<h2>Philippe Andr Joseph de Ltombe to John Adams: A Translation</h2>
 
<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Paris, 28 February 1781</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Ten days ago Mr. Searle gave me the letter that your Excellency had the honor to write me on the 3rd of January.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA11d137n1" id="PJA11d137n1-ptr">1</a> I could not answer it right away because business, events, and a thousand other obstacles prevented me from doing so. But I saw Mr. Searle as often as I could and would like to thank your Excellency for his remembrance to me and for the introduction to such an estimable citizen as Mr. Searle. I regret very much that I will not be able to cultivate our relationship any further because he is leaving for Holland and I am going to America in twelve days.</p>
<p>I ask your Excellency to honor me with the orders for Philadelphia and Boston. Be certain that it will be with much zeal and enthusiasm that I execute my post in America. Again I would like to ask that you recommend me to your compatriots. This would be a great honor. I beg you, sir, to please send the packet along to me as soon as possible in Paris, where I will find it upon my return from a ten-day trip that I must make.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA11d137n2" id="PJA11d137n2-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>Please, sir, accept my tributes of respect and of a tender attachment with which I am, your Excellency, your very humble and very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer">
<div class="signed-multiple">
    <p class="signed multiple">De Ltombe<br/>Ecuyer, Consul gnral de France  Boston.<br/>Rue de lUniversit  Paris.</p>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
